						               													<description>In odds &amp;amp; even, a trick-taking game, the cards have different suit backs depending upon if the number on the front is odd or even.  In each hand, rather than a suit being trump, either odd or even numbers are trump.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player is dealt a hand which is half odd cards and half even cards. The players look at the half which is not trump and makes a bid on how many tricks they will win this hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then, each player picks up their trump cards and drafts them, choosing 1 and passing the others, until there are no cards to pass.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players complete a number of rounds equal to the number of players and earn points for hitting their bid and other ways.  The player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
